/confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/x/XxF1X</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-01.SD:AccountListing(10xOnly)-OperationalImpacts">Operational =
Impacts</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-01.SD:AccountListing(10xOnly)-Logging:"><span style=3D"color: =
rgb(23,43,77);">Logging:</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">The recommended logging framework =
to use for API development is<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class=3D"external=
-link" href=3D"http://www.slf4j.org/" rel=3D"nofollow">SLF4J</a><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">, and it has<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class=
=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/plugins/ser=
vlet/search?q=3Dproject%3AWDP+slf4j" rel=3D"nofollow">widest adoption</a><s=
pan style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>across WDP platform =
APIs as of March 2020: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/dis=
play/WDPIPAAS/Logging+Framework+-+Java" rel=3D"nofollow">Read more</a> .</s=
pan></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">As a general concern, we should ma=
sk any <strong><u>PII</u></strong> data or <u><strong>sensitive</strong> </=
u>identifiers. In this solution, we have two data elements we should mask p=
er below table.</span></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" data-snooker-col-se=
ries=3D"numbers" data-snooker-locked-cols=3D"0" style=3D"width: 73.4124%;">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 3.34895%;">
<col style=3D"width: 26.785%;">
<col style=3D"width: 69.8661%;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTh" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" scope=3D"col"><br></th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Data Element</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Masking Strategy</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">accountId.accountNumber</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>All digits of any account number should be masked in the logger using 6 =
star (<strong>*</strong>) for all digits except the last 4 digits.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<p>Before masking:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">accountId: {
=09BSB: "035845",
=09accountNumber: "123456789"
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>After masking:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">accountId: {
=09BSB: "035845",
=09accountNumber: "******6789"
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">entityName</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p>All entity name within the array should be masked in the logger using 6 =
star (<strong>*</strong>) all letters except the last 6 letters.</p>
<p>Example:</p>
<p>Before masking:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">entityName: "=
Ali Hosseini Ltd",</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>After masking:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Midnight" data-theme=3D"Midnight">entityName: *=
******ni Ltd"</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"id-01.SD:AccountListing(10xOnly)-Security:"><span style=3D"color:=
 rgb(23,43,77);">Security:</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">In addition to client side data va=
lidation, server side validation should also be performed to ensure that th=
e correct request is being received from the UI. The&nbsp;<a class=3D"exter=
nal-link" href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/UI-WWW1/rep=
os/wdp-ui-expcommon/browse/packages/bootstrap" rel=3D"nofollow">@wdpui/comm=
on-middleware</a><span>&nbsp;</span>package (part of @wdpui/common-bootstra=
p) provides some middleware to enhance the security of experience APIs. The=
 common bootstrap is required to be used in all projects unless an exemptio=
n is received from ISG.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpa=
c.com.au/display/MESH/6.3.8+Security" rel=3D"nofollow">Read more here</a>.<=
/span></p>
