<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" style=3D"text-align: left;">4</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Create mock API f=
or the downstream APIs to be used by the the API while downstream APIs is g=
etting finalised and built;</p><p>Learn more here: <a class=3D"" href=3D"ht=
tps://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/x/1CBQTg" rel=3D"nofollow">https://conf=
luence.srv.westpac.com.au/x/1CBQTg</a></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Account engineering =
team</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" style=3D"text-align: left;">5</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Refactor code the=
 accommodate the downstream system integration when they are available</p><=
/td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Account engineering =
team</td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td class=3D"numberingColumn confluenceTd" contenteditable=3D"false" data-m=
ce-resize=3D"false" style=3D"text-align: left;">6</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Deployment;</p><p=
>A specific build must have been deployed into a lower environment before i=
t can be promoted to a higher environment. All non-production environments =
are developer self-serve, and can be triggered through Westpac Mesh Develop=
er Tools.</p><p>The order of environments is:</p><p>DEV =E2=86=92 SIT =E2=
=86=92 UAT =E2=86=92 SVP =E2=86=92 PROD</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Account engineering =
team</td>
</tr>
